        "category_index": 3,
        "goal": "No goal defined.",
        "relevance": "Without a strong username policy, users may choose predictable or easily guessable identifiers (e.g., 'admin'). This test evaluates the application's enforcement of naming conventions to prevent trivial account discovery.",
        "full_summary": "No summary provided.",
        "full_text": "",
        "methodology": "No methodology defined.",
        "tools": "No specific tools mentioned.",
        "expected_evidence": "Registration of accounts using reserved, system-critical names (e.g., admin, system) or names with whitespaces that collide with existing accounts due to faulty normalization (case sensitivity).",
        "reporting_hints": "The PoC must show the registered account and its disruptive effect. Remediation: Hardcoded blocklists for reserved names, strict special character restrictions, and proper string normalization.",
        "sysreptor_finding": "WSTG-IDNT-05: Testing for Weak or Unenforced Username Policy",
        "title_de": "Testen auf schwache oder nicht durchgesetzte Benutzernamenrichtlinien",
